OL,6,FMs Duong said Mrs Barton's bloody nose
OL,7,Fwas "an injury that really requires an
OL,8,Fexplanation", adding: "It was,
OL,9,Fplainly, something not caused by an
OL,10,Faccident."
OL,12,FBarton previously told the court he
OL,13,Fadmitted getting into an argument with
OL,14,Fhis wife, but denied that anything
OL,15,F"physical" had happened.
OL,17,FHe was arrested in his bedroom on the
OL,18,Fnight of the incident, where he had
OL,19,Fbeen asleep and was still drunk, the
OL,20,Ftrial was told.
